EVENT REMINDER: THE STORY OF THE LOST LIBRARY
----------------------------------------------------------------------

    Once upon a time a Prince made Orleans House his home; he loved
    books and built a library where he could house his large collection
    and read in peace. When he left Orleans House for France he took
    his prized books with him, years later his library was demolished
    by gravel merchants. Today, the woodland has grown and covered
    where the library once stood.

